    active_lock_reason: null,
    body:
      "Just noticed while reading through and fuzzing code, the code in Dec.Power looks like this\r\nhttps://github.com/cosmos/cosmos-sdk/blob/6a624c3f68900e99255846b4a63fb79285af54ce/types/decimal.go#L375-L390\r\n\r\nnotice the condition to decrement and check bits divides i differently depending on whether it is odd or even as per\r\nhttps://github.com/cosmos/cosmos-sdk/blob/6a624c3f68900e99255846b4a63fb79285af54ce/types/decimal.go#L381-L386\r\n\r\n## Improvement\r\nGiven that we are dealing with bits, it doesn't matter whether it is odd or even, with the same bit size, a right shift will only keep the most significant bits, so doesn't matter if it is odd or even:\r\n3 >> 1 is the same as 2 >> 1, ditto for 96 >> 1 == 97 >> 1 and we can succinctly make it\r\n```go\r\nfunc (d Dec) Power(power uint64) Dec {\r\n\tif power == 0 {\r\n\t\treturn OneDec()\r\n\t}\r\n\ttmp := OneDec()\r\n\tfor i := power; i > 1; {\r\n\t\tif i%2 != 0 {\r\n\t\t\ttmp = tmp.Mul(d)\r\n\t\t}\r\n                 i /= 2\r\n\t\td = d.Mul(d)\r\n\t}\r\n\treturn d.Mul(tmp)\r\n}\r\n```\r\nor for brevity with bit operations\r\n```go\r\nfunc (d Dec) Power(power uint64) Dec {\r\n\tif power == 0 {\r\n\t\treturn OneDec()\r\n\t}\r\n\ttmp := OneDec()\r\n\tfor i := power; i > 1; {\r\n\t\tif i&1 != 0 {\r\n\t\t\ttmp = tmp.Mul(d)\r\n\t\t}\r\n                 i >>= 1\r\n\t\td = d.Mul(d)\r\n\t}\r\n\treturn d.Mul(tmp)\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nand this algorithm brings back memories to me from more than 6 years ago with https://github.com/odeke-em/utils/blob/9a0ed5bb4a2809d0a442e1a74c71edd9563f84cf/arithmetic/utils.c#L33-L48 :)\r\n\r\n## For Admin Use\r\n\r\n- [x] Not duplicate issue\r\n- [x] Appropriate labels applied\r\n- [x] Appropriate contributors tagged\r\n- [x] Contributor assigned/self-assigned\r\n",
